{
  "answers": {
    "Q1": "The proposed architecture uses Client-Server with Layered design. The Presentation Layer handles UI and user interactions. The Business Layer contains core business logic like booking rules. The Data Access Layer handles database operations. This architecture provides separation of concerns and easier maintenance.",
    "Q2": "The issues are: 1) Incorrect layer ordering - Database is above Business layer. 2) Direct connection from UI to Database. The corrected architecture should be: Presentation -> Business -> Data Access -> Database. This improves maintainability by ensuring proper dependency flow.",
    "Q3": "The bounded contexts are: 1) Booking Context - handles ticket reservations with Booking and Ticket entities. 2) Flight Management - manages schedules with Flight and Aircraft entities. 3) Payment Context - processes payments with Payment and Transaction entities. 4) User Management - handles authentication with User and Role entities."
  }
}

